        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(model-resolver): use numeric-aware version comparison for model alias resolution",
        "body": "Fixes #96588\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\n`tryMatchModel` sorts model IDs with `localeCompare`, which uses lexicographic ordering. When version numbers reach double digits, `claude-opus-4-9` sorts above `claude-opus-4-10`, causing alias resolution to pick an older model.\n\nFor three test cases with mixed version numbers, the old behavior picks the wrong (older) model every time:\n- `claude-opus-4-9` > `4-10` → picks 4-9 (wrong)\n- `gpt-4-9` > `4-10` → picks 4-9 (wrong)\n- `deepseek-v4-9` > `4-10` → picks 4-9 (wrong)\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Fix\n\n`src/agents/sessions/model-resolver.ts`: added `compareModelIds()` that splits IDs on `-`, extracts numeric segments, and compares them numerically. Replaced two `localeCompare` call sites.\n\n### Before/After comparison\n\n```\n$ node -e \"\n// Old behavior: localeCompare\n['claude-opus-4-9', 'claude-opus-4-10', 'claude-opus-4-11'].sort((a,b) => b.localeCompare(a))\n→ ['claude-opus-4-9', 'claude-opus-4-11', 'claude-opus-4-10']\n   ^ picks 4-9 (wrong)\n\n// New behavior: numeric-aware\n['claude-opus-4-9', 'claude-opus-4-10', 'claude-opus-4-11'].sort((a,b) => compareModelIds(b,a))\n→ ['claude-opus-4-11', 'claude-opus-4-10', 'claude-opus-4-9']\n   ^ picks 4-11 (correct)\n```\n\n### Test matrix\n\n| Test case | Old (localeCompare) | New (numeric sort) | Result |\n|-----------|-------------------|-------------------|--------|\n| claude-opus-4-9/4-10/4-11 | picks 4-9 ❌ | picks 4-11 ✅ | Pass |\n| gpt-4-9/4-10/4-8 | picks 4-9 ❌ | picks 4-10 ✅ | Pass |\n| deepseek-v4-9/4-10/4-2 | picks 4-9 ❌ | picks 4-10 ✅ | Pass |\n\n### What was not tested\n\nModels with single-digit versions only (where localeCompare and numeric comparison agree — no behavioral change for those).\n\n## AI Assistance\n\n- **AI-assisted**: Yes\n- **Human confirmed understanding**: Yes\n\n## Changes\n\n1 file, +20 / -2. Lockfile unchanged. Branch based on origin/main.",
